Demo

Registration: Register a new user, then log in using a password and TOTP (Google Authenticator or similar).

File Encryption: Upload a file and encrypt it with a password. The encrypted file will be stored, and its hash will be logged in the blockchain.

Blockchain: Navigate to the blockchain page to view all events (login, file encryption) recorded in the blockchain.

Mining: After events are logged, mine new blocks into the blockchain using Proof of Work, which solves a nonce.

Security Considerations
Passwords are hashed using bcrypt.
TOTP (Time-based One-Time Password) is used for multi-factor authentication.
Files are encrypted using AES-GCM and verified with HMAC for integrity.
The blockchain ensures that actions (such as login and file encryption) cannot be tampered with.



